    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1421604/files/BertiFigure3Large.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00002 On September 14, 2015, similar signals were observed in both of LIGO's interferometers. The top panels show the measured signal in the Hanford (top left) and Livingston (top right) detectors. The bottom panels show the expected signal produced by the merger of two black holes, based on numerical simulations. [Credit: B. P. Abbott et al. [1].]</subfield>
